            "\"After Captain Hawkins passed away, we tore his treasure map into nine pieces.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"The plan was, when nobody was looking for us any more, we'd get together and go dig it up.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Splitting up the map was my idea - that way nobody could doublecross the others.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"I figure after all these years the others must have given up, so its alright for me to search for the treasure by myself.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Trouble is, I've got a bit of the gout in one leg, and I can't travel much any more.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Maybe we can help each other out.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"I know where my piece of the map is hidden, and if you bring me the other eight pieces, perhaps we could make a deal.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"I'll tell you all I know about where the pieces might be...\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Ol' Hawknose set out for the Dry Land, to kill the daemon that is said to live there.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Sandy, the ship's cook, went to Trinsic with the first mate.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Old Ybarra said he was headed for the dungeon Shame, looking for more treasure.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"I think one of the men died in a shipwreck.\"",
            "WAIT",
            "\n\n\"Then there was one more... Can't remember his name, but I've heard tell he settled in Jhelom.\"",
            "WAIT",
